2. Xenova clap-htsat-unfused tokenizer (bundled via include_bytes!)

clapkit embeds `tokenizer.json` in the crate (`assets/tokenizer.json`, exposed
as `clapkit::BUNDLED_TOKENIZER`) — byte-for-byte the same artifact textclap
pins, so tokenization is identity-comparable. Because it is compiled into the
crate, any binary linking clapkit redistributes it.

  Source: https://huggingface.co/Xenova/clap-htsat-unfused
  Revision (commit SHA): c28f2883575e590e04d3146ff0713c2448d691ba
  Artifact: tokenizer.json
  SHA-256: dc239041d98de27ffc3975473a1a23e3db4c937b23c138c38bbc66588bd247e5

  The artifact is the CLAP tokenizer configuration and vocabulary/merges — the
  RoBERTa (roberta-base, MIT lineage) tokenizer as packaged for the
  transformers.js / ONNX export; it carries no model weights. A redistributor
  should honor the upstream Xenova export's terms and the RoBERTa tokenizer's
  MIT license for the configuration.
